				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I would actually recommend testing both vblank and sprite 0 hit together in the second wait loop:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp;lda #%11000000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;bit $2002<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;beq :-</div><br />If done correctly it should only ever exit the loop due to sprite 0 hit, but vblank is an appropriate fall-back in case some disaster causes that sprite 0 to miss. The fallback result wouldn't be pretty, probably it will drop to 50% framerate and be scrolled completely wrong, etc. but the game won't lock up, and if the player can manage to get themselves where it gets restored, they can get back on track without having to abandon and reset.<br /><br />Just in case, might also be worth saying that you can have &quot;opaque&quot; pixels hit that are the same colour as the background, they just can't be colour index 0. Also the sprite background priority bit doesn't affect the hit test so you can put it &quot;under&quot; the background to hide it as well.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
